407
Title:
Commoner body
Description:
Commoner body. Dusty orange wide sleeve tunic, natural waist cloth, blue front tie ribbon; block hands; red pantaloons tuck into boots, natural shin, black shoe. 3 rods.
Notes:
Packed with 408, 409. Pencil note: "" "country inn [?] keep [?] type". Corresponds to Ch. Cat. 2b 8. " ". Both docs have written with radical. Red pencil: "".
Subjects:
Male body
Dimensions:
H: 8 x5 ; neck rod 12, hand rods 9 .
